00:04:40.840 --> 00:04:44.730
natural immune response after tissue injury, and

82
00:04:44.760 --> 00:04:48.620
what does it look like in a healing wound versus a non-healing wound

83
00:04:48.900 --> 00:04:52.870
characterized by fibrosis and inflammation, and can we use this information

84
00:04:52.900 --> 00:04:56.170
to redirect that non-healing wound to a healing environment?

85
00:04:57.020 --> 00:05:00.480
And this has applications in cartilage and fibrosis,

86
00:05:00.980 --> 00:05:01.260
and

87
00:05:02.340 --> 00:05:06.180
we recognize that the tumor was described many years ago as

88
00:05:06.280 --> 00:05:07.540
a non-healing wound.

89
00:05:08.900 --> 00:05:12.120
In a healing wound, we can look at things like muscle and pro-regenerative

