97
00:05:42.780 --> 00:05:46.540
But senescence is also a part of the wound-healing

98
00:05:46.640 --> 00:05:47.300
process.

99
00:05:48.200 --> 00:05:49.420
So in a healing wound,

100
00:05:50.320 --> 00:05:54.240
you'll have senescence initially increase and then decrease.

101
00:05:54.640 --> 00:05:58.380
But in a non-healing wound or a wound characterized by chronic

102
00:05:58.440 --> 00:06:02.220
inflammation, senescence or markers of senescence remain

103
00:06:02.280 --> 00:06:05.856
high.So senescence in hard-to-repair

