140
00:08:07.636 --> 00:08:11.296
production or related to the

141
00:08:11.576 --> 00:08:15.136
diseases associated with aging, such as heart disease, diabetes,

142
00:08:15.876 --> 00:08:19.696
and arthritis, as I mentioned. However, these cells are also

143
00:08:19.716 --> 00:08:23.296
recognized to be an important part of embryological development and tissue

144
00:08:23.316 --> 00:08:26.556
repair. So how are these cells both good and bad?

145
00:08:27.636 --> 00:08:31.576
Well, research has shown that senescent cells are a part of wound

146
00:08:31.596 --> 00:08:32.005
healing,

147
00:08:32.896 --> 00:08:36.576
and that is through secretion of PDGF,

148
00:08:36.906 --> 00:08:38.656
platelet-derived growth factor.

149
00:08:38.687 --> 00:08:42.066
And then our work on senescence as an example where

150
00:08:42.116 --> 00:08:45.856
the accumulation of senescence is associated with

151
00:08:45.896 --> 00:08:48.636
disease in the joint and arthritis.

152
00:08:49.536 --> 00:08:51.016
So from the arthritis perspective,

153
00:08:51.876 --> 00:08:55.616
we looked at an injury, anterior cruciate ligament

154
00:08:56.336 --> 00:08:59.956
transection, where the cartilage lining the

155
00:09:00.016 --> 00:09:03.606
