00:41:50.786 --> 00:41:54.586
least here, innate immune activation, neutrophils, macrophages,

716
00:41:54.646 --> 00:41:58.486
and NK cells, induced in part by these SAS molecules shown here.

717
00:41:59.206 --> 00:42:02.866
So this SAS can induce innate immune surveillance to regress

718
00:42:02.946 --> 00:42:06.396
established tumors. More recently, Scott Lowe's group has looked

719
00:42:06.526 --> 00:42:10.506
actually not at the secretome, but at the surfaceome of senescent cells, what is

720
00:42:10.566 --> 00:42:12.126
on their surface that's upregulated.

721
00:42:12.606 --> 00:42:16.126
They found the interferon gamma receptor is highly upregulated on

722
00:42:16.146 --> 00:42:18.686
