00:42:29.526 --> 00:42:33.326
and also dendritic cells to be more antigen-presenting, and thereby also

727
00:42:33.406 --> 00:42:36.846
activating adaptive CD8 T cell surveillance.

728
00:42:37.636 --> 00:42:41.606
And a back-to-back paper that came out from Manu Serrano's group even showed

729
00:42:42.066 --> 00:42:46.006
that you could inject these senescent cells as a vaccine

730
00:42:46.066 --> 00:42:49.806
into mice as a prophylactic. So if you injected these cells, then

731
00:42:49.866 --> 00:42:52.046
transplanted a tumor, the tumor never formed.

732
00:42:52.746 --> 00:42:56.006
Again, showing that senescent cells can be inherently

733
00:42:56.066 --> 00:42:59.406
immunogenic.And there's also the context of acute

734
00:42:59.446 --> 00:43:02.886
therapy-induced senescence from many different types of therapies.

735
00:43:02.926 --> 00:43:06.746
So this is really nice work from Jim Jackson's group looking at chemotherapy in

736
00:43:06.826 --> 00:43:10.726
breast cancer models. They showed that downstream of NF-kappa B

737
00:43:11.226 --> 00:43:14.646
and IRFs, a number of immunomodulatory receptors upregulating,

738
00:43:14.746 --> 00:43:17.546
including a number of different immune checkpoints.

739
00:43:17.586 --> 00:43:21.306
And they found by combining chemotherapy with

740
00:43:21.346 --> 00:43:25.286
anti PD-1 plus anti-CTLA4, which

741
00:43:25.326 --> 00:43:28.986
