1417
01:22:36.190 --> 01:22:39.930
alleles. The result is same. We see senescence in

1418
01:22:39.970 --> 01:22:43.690
response to NMU, and this senescence can be eliminated

1419
01:22:43.730 --> 01:22:47.690
by senlytic only in p53 proficient cells.

1420
01:22:48.310 --> 01:22:51.310
Now we took this to the next level and did this in vivo.

1421
01:22:51.410 --> 01:22:55.210
So we treated mice, normal C57 black 6 mice with

1422
01:22:55.390 --> 01:22:58.770
NMU. We get, among other things, RAS

1423
01:22:58.870 --> 01:23:02.770
activating mutations. And all these mice will succumb to

1424
01:23:02.810 --> 01:23:06.670
T-cell lymphomas in a limited period of time, as

1425
01:23:06.710 --> 01:23:10.370
you can see. If you use a background here, Suva

1426
01:23:10.490 --> 01:23:14.470
minus mice, which can no longer establish this H3K9

1427
01:23:14.530 --> 01:23:18.350
trimethylation mark. So they get instantly with no tumor

1428
01:23:18.360 --> 01:23:21.470
blocking senescence, these T-cell lymphomas.

1429
01:23:21.750 --> 01:23:24.780
If you do this in wild-type mice, it's much less

1430
01:23:24.830 --> 01:23:28.110
impressive. About half of the mice will get over time

1431
01:23:28.810 --> 01:23:31.630
T-cell lymphomas because there's a senescence barrier.

1432
01:23:31.710 --> 01:23:35.630
But if you now provide senlytic after NMU provision to

1433
01:23:35.650 --> 01:23:39.410
these mice, you virtually prevent tumor formation

1434
01:23:39.570 --> 01:23:43.090
from incipient RAS lesions in

1435
01:23:43.150 --> 01:23:47.110
this animal. So with this, let me conclude that we look

1436
01:23:47.190 --> 01:23:51.070
at senlytic as a novel compound class that is activated

1437
01:23:51.110 --> 01:23:54.790
by and kills via senescence-associated oxidative

1438
01:23:55.009 --> 01:23:58.810
stress. It has senolytic activity across virtually all types

1439
01:23:58.910 --> 01:24:02.250
of senescence with no obvious systemic

1440
01:24:02.330 --> 01:24:05.810
toxicity. It extends lifespan, I didn't show that, and

1441
01:24:05.850 --> 01:24:08.030
attenuates age-related pathologies.

1442
01:24:08.230 --> 01:24:12.070
Prolonged survival after debulking chemotherapy, limits the

1443
01:24:12.110 --> 01:24:15.530
progression of BRAF positive nevi to full-blown

1444
01:24:15.590 --> 01:24:19.470
melanoma, eliminates OIS restored melanoma.

1445
01:24:19.650 --> 01:24:22.470
I didn't show that, but you see the bullet point here.

1446
01:24:22.500 --> 01:24:26.190
And it prevents RAS-driven tumor formation by eliminating

1447
01:24:26.270 --> 01:24:30.170
incipient OIS lesions. So in summary, what does it mean for

1448
01:24:30.230 --> 01:24:32.310
senolysis and pre-cancer?

1449
01:24:33.330 --> 01:24:37.010
We can target an universal core feature of senescent

1450
01:24:37.030 --> 01:24:40.570
cells here, and metabolic imbalance by an pan-senolytic

1451
01:24:40.770 --> 01:24:44.450
that's feasible and effective. And using a short pulse dose

1452
01:24:44.550 --> 01:24:47.670
schedule achieves clearance of senescent cells in vivo,

1453
01:24:49.050 --> 01:24:52.730
whose proof is in clinical routine, certainly not trivial.

1454
01:24:53.370 --> 01:24:56.430
Pan-senolysis covers multiple detrimental features

1455
01:24:56.990 --> 01:25:00.930
of senescence, and I'm not seeing an advantage

1456
01:25:00.990 --> 01:25:04.870
of a more selective senolytic approach, and that's of course open to a

1457
01:25:04.950 --> 01:25:06.250
controversial discussion.

1458
01:25:07.070 --> 01:25:10.750
Cancer preventive and aging attenuation treatments may require

1459
01:25:10.850 --> 01:25:14.830
repetitive applications, and I can't tell you today, but I expect that

1460
01:25:14.890 --> 01:25:18.510
in the range of every 6 to 12 months to be needed.

1461
01:25:18.930 --> 01:25:22.770
No overt toxicity was observed, but long-term effects need to

1462
01:25:22.810 --> 01:25:26.150
be monitored, especially upon repeated applications.

1463
01:25:26.490 --> 01:25:29.750
With this, I think I have mentioned in particular the colleagues who

1464
01:25:29.790 --> 01:25:33.690
contribute to this work, and like to finish my presentation

1465
01:25:33.730 --> 01:25:34.850
to this double-edged

1466
